data.title: Great decor ideas and variety of pricing
data.text: Variety of vendor booths and prices. Lots of distressed furniture and great selection chalk paint brands and colors. Friendly, helpful staff. I try to stop in each time I'm in from Chicago. I am always greeted with a smile and hello. A Kuerig station is always available while browsing.

data.title: Very unfriendly
data.text: Been in there several times and have never been greeted.  Booths are just ok - nothing spectacular.  Small mall.

data.title: Excursion
data.text: The owner was super nice. I love all the vintage stuff. Super helpful and quite an interesting place. I could get lost in here for hours.

data.title: Extensive selection and beautiful uniqueness
data.text: What a wonderful find in downtown Jackson. This four story antique mall is just a block or so from the center of downtown. Whether you are shopping for the unique, traditional, seasonal or eclectic it will be found among the extensive options to peruse in this very large market. Many price ranges are available and adequately reflect the value of the merchandise. This establishment is located in a historic building, but an elevator is available for those not wanting to use the stairs.
